  {
    "role": "system",
    "content": "You are a Senior RAP Compliance Reviewer with deep expertise in Statement of Work (SOW) auditing.\n\nYour job is to forensically review the ENTIRE SOW document against the RAP rules provided.\n\nYou MUST check all of the following RAP compliance areas:\n1. SCOPE — Are there open-ended statements? Phrases like \"as requested\", \"as needed\", \"as necessary\" are violations. Scope must have clear boundaries.\n2. DELIVERABLES — Are all deliverables explicitly listed? Vague deliverables like \"provide documentation as necessary\" are violations. Each deliverable must be specific and measurable.\n3. OUT-OF-SCOPE — Is there an explicit Out-of-Scope section? Simply saying \"anything not listed is out of scope\" is NOT acceptable. A dedicated section with specific exclusions is required.\n4. MILESTONES/PHASES — For engagements over 3 months, are phases or milestones defined? Open-ended engagements without milestones are violations.\n5. TIMELINE — Is the timeline tied to specific deliverables? \"12 months of support\" with no delivery checkpoints is a violation.\n6. STAFFING — Is staffing appropriate for the scope? Is there architect oversight? Backup staffing? Phase-based allocation?\n7. MARGIN — Can margin compliance be verified from the SOW? If cost/rate details are missing, flag it.\n\nFor each violation found, assign a severity:\n- high: Core RAP policy broken, SOW would be rejected\n- medium: Significant gap, needs correction before approval\n- low: Minor issue or best-practice recommendation\n\nEXAMPLE OF A CORRECT OUTPUT (use this exact schema):\n[\n  {\n    \"page_number\": 3,\n    \"category\": \"Scope\",\n    \"violation_title\": \"Open-Ended Scope Language\",\n    \"quote_text\": \"perform tasks as requested by the client\",\n    \"reason\": \"The phrase 'as requested' creates unlimited scope with no defined boundaries, violating RAP Scope policy.\",\n    \"severity\": \"high\",\n    \"recommendation\": \"Replace with explicit task list: 'Perform the following tasks: [Task A], [Task B], [Task C]. All other tasks are out of scope.'\"\n  }\n]\n\nThink step by step through each section of the document. Be thorough and specific."
  },
  {
    "role": "user",
    "content": "RAP RULES TO ENFORCE:\n# RAP Review Guidlines\n\n## General\n- Verify the Scope Refer [[## Scope]] section for the rules\n- `Timelines`: Can the scope be delivered within the timeline that is mentioned\n- `Skillset : Can the scope be delivered by DevOps & Migration India Delivery team?\n- `Staffing`: Roes it have necessary staffing? If its a large engagement, and India only Engineering team, is it validated the need of having US Engineer to support the customer collaboration at US times?\n- `Delivery Responsibilities`: Clearly articulates the responsibilities of Presidio & customer w.r.t to the scope?\n- `Assumptions`: Any assumptions, over and above “Delivery Assumptions” are to be added?\n- `Special requests`: Such as working hours or type, are they mentioned explicitly? If present, does the cost is increased or adjusted according to the special request. Discuss this with Delivery Leads to confirm on the special request & costing\n- `Project Deliverables`: Explicit mention of deliverables (According to pricing model)\n- `Out Of Scope`: Explicitly mention all Out-of-scope items\n\n## Scope\n- Scope Boundaries: Are Scope boundaries clearly defined based on the pricing model?\n- No open ended statements, and high level language\n- Phases or milestones are defined?\n- If there are larger goals and scope which involves other practices, do we have good understanding of what are the responsibilities of DevOps & Migration team?\n\nII. Staffing, Costing & SPW:\n\nIf there are multiple architects (within Cloud & DevOps) segregated into streams, have we validated the need of it? to ensure there is enough clarity of responsibilities and ensure there are no challenges during delivery.\nIf there are multiple PMs, have we validated the need of it ? To ensure clarity in responsibilities\nStaffing Allocation: Is the staffing allocation meeting the minimal criteria? as outlined here \nFeedback & Lessons Learnt | Staffing Allocation \nIndia Margin: Is the India Margin above 55 - 60% ?\nStaffing: \nPhased Staffing: Has staffing plan made appropriate to the project phase and milestones? Such as: \nIf its a migration engagement, there will be a need of only 1-2 Senior\\Lead Engineers with half or full-time allocation to work with architects. Other engineers should be staffed according to the phases and need\nRight Team: Staffing done with the right set of team members required to deliver?\n\n\n## Shadowing & Travel: \n- For large engagements, that are scheduled for 3-6 months or more and with min of 3-5 member team size, shadowing hours must be included in the SOW & SPW as mentioned here\n- For scope with larger team in India, there might be a need of traveling across locations. To add travel expenses or the SPW cost rate can be increase for the engineers to account for the traveling. Please discuss this with Deliver Leads\n\n\nFULL SOW DOCUMENT:\n[Page 1]\nOpp Number & Rev:\n1003625034889.2\nAccount Manager:\nAndrew Amoruso\nPricing Summary\nCustomer Name/ID:\nNR Technology Group, LLC\nInside Sales Rep:\nContract Value\n$137,280.00\nTerritory:\n163 New York City Named\nPreSales Owner:\nOpportunity Name:\nContract Extension - AWS Engineer #2 - Vignesh\n\n[Page 2]\nScope Created by:\nPandiarajan Babu\n3rd Party Payments\n$0.00\nDate:\n11/04/25\nRate Card:\nNew York City\nNet Sell Price\n$137,280.00\nProject Name:\nContract Extension\nMilestone Type\nCUSTOM\nService Type:\nPOD\n\n[Page 3]\nMS customer\nSolution Total Cost\n$48,000.00\nPeriod of Performance:\nAWS Market Place\nSolution GP ($)\n$89,280.00\n# of Sites:\neRate FRN\nSolution GM (%)\n65.03%\n\n[Page 4]\nPrimary Cloud\nPresales Repository Link: https://presidio.sharepoint.com/sites/dept-eng/PreSales%20Customer%20Repository/Northeast Ops/N\nPresidio Internal\nInvoice Date\nPractice\nQty\nPart #\nPercent\nBaseline Hours\nCost\n\n[Page 5]\nPrice\n12/17/25\nModern Platforms\nPS-SVC-MP-POD\n160\n$4,000.00\n$11,440.00\n1/17/26\nModern Platforms\nPS-SVC-MP-POD\n160\n$4,000.00\n$1